decks.notes: This deck focuses on assembling a toolbox of creatures through combo interactions, allowing for versatile and powerful plays. Using cards like Delighted Halfling and Nadu, Winged Wisdom, the deck can generate value and control the board. With support from cards like Chord of Calling and Shuko, the deck can search for and tutor specific creatures to suit the situation. The key strategy is to outvalue and outpace the opponent by assembling the right creatures at the right time, and utilizing combo pieces to their full potential.

This Mardu Aggro deck focuses on quickly getting creatures onto the battlefield to put pressure on the opponent. It utilizes cards like Orcish Bowmasters and Amped Raptor to deal damage quickly, while Guide of Souls and Ocelot Pride provide additional support for the aggro strategy. The inclusion of Thoughtseize and Static Prison allows for disruption of the opponent's game plan, helping to maintain control of the board. With strong creatures like Phlage, Titan of Fire's Fury and Ajani, Nacatl Pariah, this deck aims to overwhelm the opponent and secure a victory through aggressive tactics.

This Mono Black Aggro deck focuses on a combination of hand disruption, removal spells, and aggressive creatures to put pressure on the opponent and control the board. Cards like Thoughtseize and Fatal Push disrupt the opponent's game plan, while creatures like Dauthi Voidwalker and Sheoldred, the Apocalypse can quickly close out the game. The deck also features some recursion with cards like Malakir Rebirth and Necrodominance, allowing for additional value and flexibility in a longer game. Overall, this deck aims to overwhelm the opponent with a combination of disruption and aggression.

This deck focuses on quickly establishing a board presence and dealing damage effectively. The key strategy involves utilizing aggressive creatures like Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer and Amped Raptor, along with support cards like Lightning Bolt and Galvanic Discharge, to overwhelm the opponent. The inclusion of Blood Moon and Static Prison adds disruption to the opponent's plans, while cards like Ajani, Nacatl Pariah provide additional strength and versatility. Overall, the deck aims to maintain pressure and tempo throughout the game, forcing the opponent to react and adapt to its aggressive strategy.

The deck focuses on controlling the game through countering spells, removing threats, and card advantage. It combines powerful counterspells like Counterspell and Spell Snare with removal spells like Lightning Bolt and Sink into Stupor to control the board. Snapcaster Mage and Tamiyo, Inquisitive Student provide card advantage and flexibility. The deck also includes card selection tools like Preordain and Expressive Iteration to maintain consistency. The game plan revolves around disrupting the opponent's strategy, maintaining control of the game, and eventually winning through powerful threats like Harbinger of the Seas and Flame of Anor.

The deck revolves around using powerful control spells and creatures to disrupt the opponent's game plan while steadily building up advantage. It focuses on hand disruption, removal, and powerful creatures to outvalue the opponent in the late game. The deck also incorporates some graveyard recursion and utility lands to generate additional value. It aims to control the game from start to finish, disrupting the opponent's strategy while presenting powerful threats of its own. Ultimately, the goal is to outlast and outvalue the opponent to secure victory.
